        return c == 'a' || c == 'e' || c == 'i' || c == 'o' || c == 'u';
    }
}
```

This code first defines an `IsVowel` method to check if a character is a vowel. Then it sorts the words using the `OrderBy` function from LINQ by counting the number of vowels in the word. Finally, it writes the sorted list of words to the console.

