Here are 10 data structures explained with example code in C#:

<h3>1. Arrays</h3>
<p>An array is an ordered collection of items that can be accessed using an integer index. Arrays are perfect for storing sequences of data that can be accessed in a predictable pattern.</p>
<pre><code>string[] names = new string[] {"Alice", "Bob", "Charlie"};</code></pre>

<p>To add a new name to the array, you can simply create a new string and assign it to a new index.</p>
<pre><code>names[names.Length] = "Daisy";</code></pre>

<p>To search for a name in the array, you can compare it to each element of the array.</p>
<pre><code>string query = "Alice";
bool found = false;
foreach (string element in names)
{
